---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BaseLayout title="Expose GitHub E-mail Address - Sara's OSINT Resources">
  <article class="prose prose-invert prose-violet max-w-none">
    <a href="/sara.osint/blog" class="mb-4 inline-block text-violet-400 hover:text-violet-300">‚Üê Back to Blog</a>
    
    <h1 class="gradient-text mb-4 text-5xl font-bold">Expose GitHub E-mail Address*</h1>
    <p class="mb-8 text-sm text-slate-500">June 2025</p>

    <div class="space-y-6 leading-relaxed">
      <p class="text-xl font-semibold">101</p>
      
      <p>
        I have my friend <a href="https://github.com/sickcodes/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Sick.Codes</a> GitHub profile. 
        With his permission, I will go through the few steps to find one's e-mail through their profile.
      </p>

      <section class="rounded-lg border border-slate-700 bg-slate-800/50 p-6">
        <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold">Step 1: Locate a Repository</h2>
        <p>
          Locate the pinned/favorited repositories and click on one of them. 
          Example: <a href="https://github.com/sickcodes/osx-serial-generator" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">osx-serial-generator</a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="rounded-lg border border-slate-700 bg-slate-800/50 p-6">
        <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold">Step 2: Click on Commit Numbers</h2>
        <p>
          Click on the commit numbers (letters/numbers) to view commit details.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="rounded-lg border border-slate-700 bg-slate-800/50 p-6">
        <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold">Step 3: Add .patch to URL</h2>
        <p>
          After a new page has opened, add <code class="rounded bg-slate-900 px-2 py-1">.patch</code> at the end of the URL and hit enter.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4">
          The output should include the target's e-mail address. <strong>Always assume you have the information until you've verified it is correct.</strong>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mt-8 rounded-lg border border-yellow-600 bg-yellow-900/20 p-6">
        <h3 class="mb-3 text-xl font-bold text-yellow-400">‚ö†Ô∏è Things to Keep in Mind:</h3>
        <p class="text-yellow-200">
          Information may NOT be accurate and could belong to another user's profile/account who has made pull requests on the repository.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mt-8">
        <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold">Web Based Tools</h2>
        <p class="mb-3">Tools that may be helpful with GitHub e-mails, IDs, usernames:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2">
          <li><a href="https://api.github.com/users/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://api.github.com/users/</a>ADDUSERNAMEHERE</li>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/search/advanced" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub Advanced Search</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://githut.info/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHut</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://recruitin.net/github.php" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Recruitin GitHub Search</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://freepeoplesearchtool.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Free People Search Tool</a></li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <p class="mt-8 text-center text-lg font-semibold text-violet-400">
        Take caution, verify your data, and keep it ethical. üíô
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
